1
00:01:23,653 --> 00:01:27,719
- POSSESSION OF THE SACRED
SHIKON JEWEL

2
00:01:27,753 --> 00:01:30,353
BESTOWS TREMENDOUS POWER
UPON DEMONS

3
00:01:30,386 --> 00:01:34,386
AND OTHERS WITH EVIL
RESIDING IN THEIR HEARTS.

4
00:01:34,419 --> 00:01:35,653
MY SISTER, KIKYO,

5
00:01:35,686 --> 00:01:38,953
HAD DIED TRYING TO SEAL
THE JEWEL'S POWERS.

6
00:01:38,986 --> 00:01:44,986
HOWEVER, SHE WAS REINCARNATED
AS A YOUNG WOMAN NAMED KAGOME,

7
00:01:45,019 --> 00:01:47,553
AND RETURNED TO COMPLETE
HER MISSION.

8
00:01:47,586 --> 00:01:51,686
NOW THE JOURNEY BEGINS
FOR INUYASHA,

9
00:01:51,719 --> 00:01:53,986
A HALF-DEMON
WITH A HUMAN MOTHER,

10
00:01:54,019 --> 00:01:59,753
AND THE YOUNG WOMAN
FROM THE MODERN AGE.

11
00:02:05,119 --> 00:02:07,753
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

12
00:02:11,053 --> 00:02:12,053
- HMM.

13
00:02:12,086 --> 00:02:15,619
CLEAR.
HERE GOES.

14
00:02:15,653 --> 00:02:17,953
- WHAT'S YOUR HURRY, KAGOME?

15
00:02:17,986 --> 00:02:18,986
UHH.
- ERK!

16
00:02:19,019 --> 00:02:20,919
- NOT SO FAST.
YOU'RE NOT GOING ANYWHERE

17
00:02:20,953 --> 00:02:23,586
UNTIL YOU HAND OVER THE SHARDS
OF THE SACRED JEWEL.

18
00:02:23,619 --> 00:02:25,253
- IN MY ERA, GIRLS GO TO SCHOOL,

19
00:02:25,286 --> 00:02:27,153
AND IT JUST SO HAPPENS
THAT THIS GIRL

20
00:02:27,186 --> 00:02:29,019
HAS A HUGE FINAL TOMORROW
TO STUDY FOR!

21
00:02:29,053 --> 00:02:32,053
MY ATTENDANCE IS SO BAD,
I MIGHT FAIL THE CLASS,

22
00:02:32,086 --> 00:02:34,019
EVEN IF I ACE THE EXAM.

23
00:02:34,053 --> 00:02:36,453
HEY! NOW WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
[GRUNTING]

24
00:02:36,486 --> 00:02:37,686
- WHAT DOES IT LOOK LIKE?

25
00:02:37,719 --> 00:02:39,086
I'M GOING TO COVER UP THE WELL
FOR GOOD.

26
00:02:39,119 --> 00:02:42,619
THEN YOU WON'T BE ABLE TO ESCAPE
TO THAT STRANGE ERA OF YOURS.

27
00:02:42,653 --> 00:02:43,953
GOOD RIDDANCE!

28
00:02:43,986 --> 00:02:44,853
- SIT!

29
00:02:44,886 --> 00:02:46,853
- HUH?
- SIT! SIT! SIT!

30
00:02:46,886 --> 00:02:49,619
SIT! SIT! SIT! SIT!
- UHH! UHH! AUGH!

31
00:02:49,653 --> 00:02:53,186
UHH! AUGH!
UHH. UHH.

32
00:02:53,219 --> 00:02:55,519
- STAY, BOY.
I'LL BE BACK IN 3 DAYS,

33
00:02:55,553 --> 00:03:00,019
AND DON'T EVEN THINK
ABOUT FOLLOWING ME!
UHH.

34
00:03:04,019 --> 00:03:07,086
- [CHANTING IN JAPANESE]

35
00:03:07,119 --> 00:03:10,119
- WHY WASTE YOUR TIME WITH THAT
CHANTING STUFF, GRANDPA?

36
00:03:10,153 --> 00:03:12,086
IT DOESN'T ACTUALLY WORK,
DOES IT?

37
00:03:12,119 --> 00:03:13,319
- IT DOES.

38
00:03:13,353 --> 00:03:14,686
THIS ANCIENT
GET-OUT-OF-THE-WELL CHANT

39
00:03:14,719 --> 00:03:19,186
HAS BEEN PASSED DOWN
THROUGH GENERATIONS
OF HIGURASHI PRIESTS.

40
00:03:19,219 --> 00:03:20,319
[LAUGHS]

41
00:03:20,353 --> 00:03:22,519
- THEN HOW COME YOU'VE BEEN
AT IT FOR 3 DAYS AND NIGHTS

42
00:03:22,553 --> 00:03:24,919
AND KAGOME STILL HASN'T
COME BACK?

43
00:03:24,953 --> 00:03:27,153
- HMM.

44
00:03:28,986 --> 00:03:30,386
- AND TOUCHDOWN.
WHOA!

45
00:03:30,419 --> 00:03:33,519
- NOW FOR THE SECRET RICE WINE.
UHH.

46
00:03:33,553 --> 00:03:35,053
- HMM?
UHH!

47
00:03:35,086 --> 00:03:38,619
WHAT IS THIS STUFF?
IT SMELLS LIKE SAKE.

48
00:03:38,653 --> 00:03:39,853
- KAGOME!
IT'S YOU!

49
00:03:39,886 --> 00:03:42,519
I KNEW MY PRAYERS
WOULD BE ANSWERED.

50
00:03:42,553 --> 00:03:44,853
- THANKS FOR WORRYING
ABOUT ME, GRAMPS.

51
00:03:44,886 --> 00:03:47,219
YOU DON'T KNOW HOW MUCH
IT MEANS TO ME.

52
00:03:47,253 --> 00:03:48,253
[AHCHOO]

53
00:03:48,286 --> 00:03:50,286
- SEE, SOTA?
I TOLD YOU IT WOULD WORK.

54
00:03:50,319 --> 00:03:52,219
- HEY, SHE'S BACK!
YOU REALLY DID IT, GRAMPS!

55
00:03:52,253 --> 00:03:54,286
- NO TIME LIKE THE PRESENT
TO SHAVE YOUR HEAD

56
00:03:54,319 --> 00:03:55,686
AND START TRAINING
FOR THE PRIESTHOOD.

57
00:03:55,719 --> 00:03:58,019
- SHAVE MY HEAD?
- OF COURSE.
TIME TO PASS THE TORCH.

58
00:03:58,053 --> 00:04:00,419
- GET REAL.
I'M GOING TO BE
A FAMOUS SOCCER PLAYER.

59
00:04:00,453 --> 00:04:01,719
- SOCCER? WHAT KIND OF A JOB
IS THAT?

60
00:04:01,753 --> 00:04:03,886
DUSTING ANTIQUES AND CHECKING
FOR POCKET CHANGE, THAT--

61
00:04:03,919 --> 00:04:06,886
- VERY INTERESTING, BUT COULD WE
FINISH THIS CONVERSATION

62
00:04:06,919 --> 00:04:08,353
AFTER YOU'VE HELPED ME
OUT OF THE WELL?

63
00:04:08,386 --> 00:04:09,753
- ANYWAY, MOM WANTS ME
TO BE A DOCTOR.

64
00:04:09,786 --> 00:04:13,019
- A DOCTOR?
WELL, I SUPPOSE YOU COULD BE
A DOCTOR ON THE WEEKENDS,

65
00:04:13,053 --> 00:04:18,086
BUT WE'RE STILL GOING
TO START YOU TRAINING
FOR THE PRIESTHOOD TODAY.

66
00:04:19,086 --> 00:04:22,853
[AHCHOO]
- WHAT'S THE PROBLEM, BUYO?
GOT A COLD OR SOMETHING?

67
00:04:22,886 --> 00:04:26,919
OR MAYBE MY HAIR STILL SMELLS
A LITTLE GROSS.
- [WHIMPERING]

68
00:04:26,953 --> 00:04:29,319
- HERE'S YOUR NEW
SCHOOL UNIFORM, KAGOME.

69
00:04:29,353 --> 00:04:30,919
I'LL PUT IT IN YOUR ROOM
FOR YOU.

70
00:04:30,953 --> 00:04:32,653
- THANKS, MOM.
LOOKS GOOD.

71
00:04:32,686 --> 00:04:34,486
- WHERE'S THAT DOG GUY INUYASHA?

72
00:04:34,519 --> 00:04:35,719
DIDN'T YOU BRING HIM HOME
WITH YOU?

73
00:04:35,753 --> 00:04:38,753
- OF COURSE I DIDN'T.
I'VE GOT BETTER THINGS TO DO

74
00:04:38,786 --> 00:04:42,553
THAN SPEND MY TIME
BABY-SITTING A DEMON ALL DAY.
HA!

75
00:04:42,586 --> 00:04:46,386
OH, BROTHER.
MY LIFE'S GETTING A BIT
TOO COMPLICATED.

76
00:04:46,419 --> 00:04:51,619
I'VE LIVED HERE
AT HIGURASHI SHRINE
SINCE I WAS 4.

77
00:04:51,886 --> 00:04:55,086
THERE'S GRAMPS, MOM,
MY LITTLE BROTHER SOTA,

78
00:04:55,119 --> 00:04:58,353
AND ME, YOUR AVERAGE
MIDDLE SCHOOL GIRL.

79
00:04:58,386 --> 00:05:00,553
BUT THAT'S WHERE THINGS
START GETTING WEIRD.

80
00:05:00,586 --> 00:05:02,419
WE HAVE A HIDDEN WELL
ON THE GROUNDS

81
00:05:02,453 --> 00:05:04,153
THAT LEADS TO THE FEUDAL ERA,

82
00:05:04,186 --> 00:05:06,053
NOT TO MENTION
ALL KINDS OF MONSTERS

83
00:05:06,086 --> 00:05:08,686
THAT ARE AFTER THE SHARDS
OF THE SHIKON JEWEL.

84
00:05:08,719 --> 00:05:13,453
NOW, ALL OF A SUDDEN,
MY LIFE IS ANYTHING BUT AVERAGE.

85
00:05:14,719 --> 00:05:16,353
I KEEP THINKING
I'M GOING TO WAKE UP

86
00:05:16,386 --> 00:05:19,053
TO FIND OUT IT'S ALL
A BAD DREAM OR SOMETHING,

87
00:05:19,086 --> 00:05:21,586
BUT IT'S NOT A DREAM.
IT'S VERY REAL,

88
00:05:21,619 --> 00:05:24,653
AND I'LL JUST HAVE TO FIND A WAY
TO DEAL WITH IT.

89
00:05:24,686 --> 00:05:27,019
[SIGH]

90
00:05:27,053 --> 00:05:28,686
RIGHT!

91
00:05:51,819 --> 00:05:53,586
[LAUGHTER]

92
00:05:53,619 --> 00:05:55,553
- HEY, WAIT UP, GUYS!

93
00:05:55,586 --> 00:05:56,619
[GASPS]
- KAGOME!

94
00:05:56,653 --> 00:05:58,953
YOU SURE YOU'RE FEELING
WELL ENOUGH TO BE AT SCHOOL?

95
00:05:58,986 --> 00:05:59,886
- HEH HEH.

96
00:05:59,919 --> 00:06:01,719
- WE HEARD ABOUT YOUR ACCIDENT
WITH THE CAT.

97
00:06:01,753 --> 00:06:04,019
THAT IS ONE NASTY PLACE
TO GET BITTEN.

98
00:06:04,053 --> 00:06:05,686
HOW'S YOUR BACK
AFTER THAT FALL OUT OF BED?

99
00:06:05,719 --> 00:06:09,419
- BEFORE YOU PUT YOUR BACK OUT,
YOU WERE AWAY FOR SOME
LYME DISEASE TESTS.

100
00:06:09,453 --> 00:06:10,419
- GOT THE RESULTS BACK YET?

101
00:06:10,453 --> 00:06:12,886
- AND WHAT ABOUT
THAT CASE OF RINGWORM?
[GROANS]

102
00:06:12,919 --> 00:06:17,286
- COME ON, GRAMPS.
COULDN'T YOU HAVE TOLD THEM
I HAVE A COLD?

103
00:06:17,319 --> 00:06:19,253
- HEY, KAGOME.

104
00:06:19,286 --> 00:06:21,453
- HUH?

105
00:06:23,086 --> 00:06:24,886
- HOW ARE YOU MAKING OUT
WITH THOSE BUNIONS?

106
00:06:24,919 --> 00:06:28,586
- HUH?
[GASPS]
- IT'S HOJO, THE MEGA-HUNK.

107
00:06:28,619 --> 00:06:32,419
- WOW, TALK ABOUT
A DOUBLE WHAMMY.

108
00:06:32,453 --> 00:06:34,253
BUNIONS AND GOUT?

109
00:06:34,286 --> 00:06:35,419
- OHH!

110
00:06:35,453 --> 00:06:38,986
- HERE, THIS IS FROM THE SHOP.
YOU KNOW, FOR YOUR AILMENTS.

111
00:06:39,019 --> 00:06:43,486
MOM WRAPPED IT UP.
I HOPE YOU LIKE PINK.
[GASPS]

112
00:06:43,519 --> 00:06:45,453
- UH...HUH?

113
00:06:45,486 --> 00:06:51,086
- THERAPEUTIC SANDALS
FOR YOUR BUNIONS.

114
00:06:52,886 --> 00:06:54,819
- OHH!
- KAGOME!

115
00:06:54,853 --> 00:06:56,786
ARE YOU GOING OUT WITH HOJO?

116
00:06:56,819 --> 00:06:59,253
- 'COURSE NOT.
I HAVEN'T GOT THE TIME.

117
00:06:59,286 --> 00:07:02,353
DOES THAT GUY TOTALLY HAVE
THE HOTS FOR YOU, OR WHAT?

118
00:07:02,386 --> 00:07:03,386
- OH, YEAH.

119
00:07:03,419 --> 00:07:05,686
- YOU MEAN, HE'S NEVER EVEN
TALKED TO YOU BEFORE?

120
00:07:05,719 --> 00:07:08,719
- NOT REALLY.
- AREN'T YOU EVEN EXCITED?

121
00:07:08,753 --> 00:07:10,519
- OH, NO.
MAYBE SHE LIKES SOMEONE ELSE.

122
00:07:10,553 --> 00:07:12,086
- COME ON.
I DON'T LIKE ANYONE.

123
00:07:12,119 --> 00:07:14,486
- IF YOU DID,
WHAT WOULD HE BE LIKE?

124
00:07:14,519 --> 00:07:17,586
THE ATHLETIC TYPE
OR THE INTELLECTUAL TYPE?

125
00:07:17,619 --> 00:07:18,853
- I DON'T KNOW.
- HUH?

126
00:07:18,886 --> 00:07:21,286
- HE DEFINITELY WOULDN'T
BE AGGRESSIVE,

127
00:07:21,319 --> 00:07:23,586
AND NOT SELFISH.

128
00:07:23,619 --> 00:07:25,486
HE WOULDN'T GET MAD EASILY.

129
00:07:25,519 --> 00:07:27,753
HE'D BE KIND AND UNDERSTANDING,

130
00:07:27,786 --> 00:07:30,486
AND HE'D BRING ME FLOWERS
AND WRITE ME POETRY.

131
00:07:30,519 --> 00:07:35,019
SOMEONE THE EXACT OPPOSITE
OF INUYASHA.

132
00:07:35,053 --> 00:07:38,219
THAT'S THE PERFECT GUY FOR ME.

133
00:07:39,486 --> 00:07:41,853
- I'LL TAKE THAT
AS AN UNDECIDED.

134
00:07:41,886 --> 00:07:44,986
- MAYBE SHE IS STILL SICK.

135
00:07:45,586 --> 00:07:49,519
[HUMMING]
- UH, UH...OHH!

136
00:07:49,553 --> 00:07:50,753
- STOP LAZING ABOUT.

137
00:07:50,786 --> 00:07:52,053
GET OFF YE DUFF AND SEEK OUT

138
00:07:52,086 --> 00:07:53,686
SOME INFORMATION
ON THE SACRED JEWEL.

139
00:07:53,719 --> 00:07:56,753
- AND IF YE HADN'T NOTICED,
MY BACK'S OUT OF COMMISSION,

140
00:07:56,786 --> 00:07:58,253
THANKS TO ALL THOSE
"SIT" COMMANDS.

141
00:07:58,286 --> 00:08:01,653
OOH, YOU JUST WAIT TILL
YOU COME BACK, KAGOME.

142
00:08:01,686 --> 00:08:06,219
YOU'RE GONNA PAY FOR THIS!
OW! OOH!

143
00:08:07,353 --> 00:08:09,653
- HUH?
SOMETHING'S SMOKING.

144
00:08:13,519 --> 00:08:15,653
THE STOREHOUSE IS ON FIRE!

145
00:08:23,219 --> 00:08:27,086
THIS IS TERRIBLE!
THE NOH MASK HAS BURNED
THROUGH THE TALISMANS

146
00:08:27,119 --> 00:08:30,853
THAT HAVE SEALED UP ITS EVIL
FOR GENERATIONS.

147
00:08:30,886 --> 00:08:36,286
- I MUST HAVE A PHYSICAL BODY.

148
00:08:39,619 --> 00:08:41,019
- UHH!

149
00:08:41,053 --> 00:08:43,053
MY GREAT-GREAT-GREAT-GREAT
GRANDFATHER

150
00:08:43,086 --> 00:08:45,553
EXORCISED THAT EVIL MASK
FOR A NOH ACTOR

151
00:08:45,586 --> 00:08:46,353
WHO BROUGHT IT TO HIM.

152
00:08:46,386 --> 00:08:48,686
IT WAS CALLED
THE FLESH-EATING MASK,

153
00:08:48,719 --> 00:08:51,653
AND WAS RUMORED TO HAVE
INCREDIBLE MALEVOLENT POWERS.

154
00:08:51,686 --> 00:08:54,819
I MUST DO EVERYTHING POSSIBLE
TO SEAL IT UP AGAIN!

155
00:08:54,853 --> 00:08:58,753
UHH...AHH!

156
00:08:59,353 --> 00:09:00,486
A BODY.

157
00:09:00,519 --> 00:09:03,386
I MUST POSSESS A BODY.

158
00:09:04,086 --> 00:09:05,919
- AAH!
UHH.

159
00:09:05,953 --> 00:09:08,786
AAH!
AAH!

160
00:09:16,119 --> 00:09:19,753
- A BODY.
I MUST POSSESS A HUMAN BODY.

161
00:09:19,786 --> 00:09:21,519
- HE'S LOOKING FOR LIVING FLESH

162
00:09:21,553 --> 00:09:24,719
TO EMBODY AND WREAK HAVOC ON US!

163
00:09:24,753 --> 00:09:26,986
AAH!

164
00:09:27,819 --> 00:09:31,253
- MY SOUL YEARNS
FOR A LIVING BODY.

165
00:09:31,286 --> 00:09:32,986
- I MUST STOP IT.

166
00:09:33,019 --> 00:09:35,019
- GIVE ME FLESH AND BLOOD!

167
00:09:35,053 --> 00:09:36,919
[RINGING]

168
00:09:36,953 --> 00:09:39,586
[SIREN WAILING]

169
00:09:42,219 --> 00:09:45,119
- HEY, DID YOU HEAR?
HIGURASHI SHRINE'S ON FIRE.

170
00:09:45,153 --> 00:09:48,186
- COOL! LET'S CHECK IT OUT!
- YEAH!

171
00:09:48,219 --> 00:09:49,086
- HUH?

172
00:09:49,119 --> 00:09:51,053
- NO PUSHING, PLEASE.
- YUP, 3 UNITS.

173
00:09:51,086 --> 00:09:53,586
- IT'S JUST A SMALL FIRE, FOLKS.
STAY BEHIND THE...

174
00:09:53,619 --> 00:09:55,786
- LET ME THROUGH.
I'VE GOT TO GET IN!

175
00:09:55,819 --> 00:09:57,486
- HEY, YOU!
THIS AREA'S OFF LIMITS!

176
00:09:57,519 --> 00:10:00,819
- THANK YOU FOR
ALL YOUR HELP, OFFICER.
- NO PROBLEM.

177
00:10:00,853 --> 00:10:01,886
- MOM!
WHAT'S GOING ON?

178
00:10:01,919 --> 00:10:04,586
- KAGOME!
- WHAT HAPPENED?
WHERE'S THE FIRE?

179
00:10:04,619 --> 00:10:06,053
- THE OLD STOREHOUSE
CAUGHT ON FIRE

180
00:10:06,086 --> 00:10:08,619
AND GRANDPA WAS TRAPPED INSIDE
IN THE SMOKE.

181
00:10:08,653 --> 00:10:09,919
- GRANDPA'S HURT?

182
00:10:09,953 --> 00:10:10,953
- OH, DON'T WORRY.

183
00:10:10,986 --> 00:10:12,253
HE'D FAINTED AND SUFFERED FROM

184
00:10:12,286 --> 00:10:13,119
A BIT OF SMOKE INHALATION,

185
00:10:13,153 --> 00:10:15,219
BUT THEY SAY 2 OR 3 DAYS
IN THE HOSPITAL

186
00:10:15,253 --> 00:10:16,186
AND HE SHOULD BE GOOD AS NEW.

187
00:10:16,219 --> 00:10:17,786
I'M JUST ON MY WAY
TO CHECK IN ON HIM

188
00:10:17,819 --> 00:10:18,819
AND SEE HOW HE'S DOING.

189
00:10:18,853 --> 00:10:20,153
- I'M GOING WITH YOU.

190
00:10:20,186 --> 00:10:22,619
- KAGOME, YOU STAY HERE
AND WAIT FOR SOTA.

191
00:10:22,653 --> 00:10:25,453
SOMEONE'S GOT TO EXPLAIN
THINGS TO HIM.

192
00:10:25,486 --> 00:10:26,319
- YEAH, OK.

193
00:10:26,353 --> 00:10:29,353
HOW COULD A FIRE START
IN THE STOREHOUSE?

194
00:10:29,386 --> 00:10:32,619
SOMETHING ABOUT THIS
DOESN'T SOUND RIGHT.

195
00:10:32,653 --> 00:10:35,553
- [SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

196
00:10:35,586 --> 00:10:38,319
- OK. YEAH, YEAH.
THERE'S SOME DAMAGE...

197
00:10:39,319 --> 00:10:40,786
- HUH?

198
00:10:41,153 --> 00:10:43,786
WHAT'S DOWN THERE?

199
00:10:51,019 --> 00:10:52,819
WHOA--
[MUFFLED SPEECH]

200
00:10:52,853 --> 00:10:56,253
- HEY, WH-WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?
WHAT'S GOING ON?

201
00:10:56,286 --> 00:10:58,553
- [MUFFLED SPEECH]

202
00:10:58,586 --> 00:11:01,186
- SAY SOMETHING!
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

203
00:11:01,219 --> 00:11:02,086
- KAGOME!

204
00:11:02,119 --> 00:11:04,886
[BREATHING HEAVILY]
- DON'T WORRY, SOTA.

205
00:11:04,919 --> 00:11:06,019
IT WASN'T IN THE MAIN SHRINE,

206
00:11:06,053 --> 00:11:08,619
AND NO ONE WAS SERIOUSLY HURT.

207
00:11:08,653 --> 00:11:10,819
[CRASH]

208
00:11:11,453 --> 00:11:13,119
- HUH?

209
00:11:15,253 --> 00:11:17,719
- STOP THE TRUCK!

210
00:11:18,086 --> 00:11:19,853
- HUH--HUH--UHH!

211
00:11:23,353 --> 00:11:24,486
- THAT WAY!
HURRY!

212
00:11:24,519 --> 00:11:26,719
- SIR, REQUESTING A CALL IN
FOR BACKUP.
- THIS JUST IN.

213
00:11:26,753 --> 00:11:28,986
A FIRE TRUCK IS DRIVING WILDLY
THROUGH THE STREETS,

214
00:11:29,019 --> 00:11:31,119
COMPLETELY OUT OF CONTROL
AND SMASHING INTO

215
00:11:31,153 --> 00:11:32,419
ANYTHING AND ANYONE IN ITS PATH.

216
00:11:32,453 --> 00:11:34,553
THE NUMBER OF INJURED SO FAR
HAS NOT BEEN CONFIRMED,

217
00:11:34,586 --> 00:11:36,586
SINCE EVERY PERSON
THAT CROSSES ITS PATH

218
00:11:36,619 --> 00:11:38,319
SEEMS TO HAVE VANISHED
INTO THIN AIR.

219
00:11:38,353 --> 00:11:39,919
THAT'S ALL THE INFORMATION
WE HAVE AT PRESENT,

220
00:11:39,953 --> 00:11:41,453
BUT UNTIL MORE IS KNOWN
ABOUT THE INCIDENT,

221
00:11:41,486 --> 00:11:44,486
WE STRONGLY ADVISE EVERYONE
TO STAY OFF THE STREETS.

222
00:11:44,519 --> 00:11:46,219
- THE FLESH IS DISINTEGRATING.

223
00:11:46,253 --> 00:11:48,453
IF I CAN FIND MORE SHARDS
OF THE SACRED JEWEL,

224
00:11:48,486 --> 00:11:51,286
I CAN GAIN THE POWER TO STOP
THIS FLESH FROM DECOMPOSING.

225
00:11:51,319 --> 00:11:57,919
THEN I WILL HAVE AN ALMIGHTY
EVERLASTING BODY
OF LIVING, PULSATING FLESH.

226
00:12:00,086 --> 00:12:01,386
- HOW'S GRANDPA?
IS HE AWAKE YET?

227
00:12:01,419 --> 00:12:03,719
- HE'S STILL UNCONSCIOUS,
BUT THE DOCTOR'S
A LITTLE BAFFLED.

228
00:12:03,753 --> 00:12:07,153
HE SAYS IT'S NOTHING SERIOUS,
SO HE EXPECTED GRANDPA TO HAVE
WOKEN UP BY NOW.

229
00:12:07,186 --> 00:12:09,519
- OH...
- I'M SURE IT'S
JUST A MATTER OF TIME.

230
00:12:09,553 --> 00:12:12,153
LET'S NOT FORGET HIS AGE
IS A FACTOR.

231
00:12:12,186 --> 00:12:13,653
- HUH?

232
00:12:14,453 --> 00:12:16,486
WHAT ARE THOSE?
LET ME SEE.

233
00:12:16,519 --> 00:12:17,986
- THESE? THEY'RE TALISMANS.

234
00:12:18,019 --> 00:12:21,386
THE FIREFIGHTERS FOUND THEM
PLASTERED OVER GRANDPA'S FACE
AND IN HIS MOUTH.

235
00:12:21,419 --> 00:12:25,153
POOR GRANDPA.
SOMETHING MUST HAVE
REALLY SPOOKED HIM.

236
00:12:25,186 --> 00:12:27,386
[MOANING]
- HUH?

237
00:12:27,419 --> 00:12:29,719
- BEWARE THE FLESH-EATING MASK.

238
00:12:29,753 --> 00:12:34,186
BEWARE THE ANCIENT
FLESH-EATING MASK.

239
00:12:36,653 --> 00:12:38,286
- SO IT'S JUST
THE TWO OF US HERE TONIGHT,

240
00:12:38,319 --> 00:12:39,886
SINCE MOM'S GOING
TO STAY AT THE HOSPITAL

241
00:12:39,919 --> 00:12:42,786
AND WATCH OVER GRANDPA
IN CASE HE WAKES UP.

242
00:12:42,819 --> 00:12:43,819
[GRUNTING]
HMM?

243
00:12:43,853 --> 00:12:47,253
- SIS, GOT ANY ROOM
FOR BUYO AND ME TO SLEEP HERE?

244
00:12:47,286 --> 00:12:49,619
- NO CHANCE.
YOU CAN STAY IN YOUR OWN ROOM.

245
00:12:49,653 --> 00:12:52,919
- PLEASE, SIS?
- DON'T BE SUCH A SCAREDY-CAT.

246
00:12:52,953 --> 00:12:55,586
I'M GOING TO BE UP ALL NIGHT
STUDYING FOR A TEST.

247
00:12:55,619 --> 00:12:56,919
THE ONLY THING YOU SHOULD
BE SCARED OF

248
00:12:56,953 --> 00:12:58,986
ARE THE DUST BUNNIES
UNDER YOUR BED.

249
00:12:59,019 --> 00:13:00,486
- WHEN GRANDPA WAS SCARED,

250
00:13:00,519 --> 00:13:02,619
HE COVERED HIS FACE
IN THOSE WRITTEN SPELLS.

251
00:13:02,653 --> 00:13:05,186
SOMETHING CREEPY
HAPPENED IN THERE, SIS.

252
00:13:05,219 --> 00:13:07,319
I JUST KNOW IT.
- HMM?

253
00:13:07,353 --> 00:13:10,219
- BEWARE THE FLESH-EATING MASK.

254
00:13:10,253 --> 00:13:12,653
- GUH--

255
00:13:13,553 --> 00:13:14,386
- SOMETHING'S WRONG.

256
00:13:14,419 --> 00:13:15,686
WE'VE NEVER HAD TROUBLE
LIKE THIS

257
00:13:15,719 --> 00:13:17,719
AT THE SHRINE BEFORE,
SO WHY NOW?

258
00:13:17,753 --> 00:13:19,619
WHY, AFTER
ALL THESE GENERATIONS?

259
00:13:19,653 --> 00:13:22,386
- HUH?
THE JEWEL SHARDS!
THAT'S IT!

260
00:13:22,419 --> 00:13:25,619
IT'S BECAUSE I BROUGHT
THE JEWEL SHARDS BACK!
[SIREN WAILING]

261
00:13:25,653 --> 00:13:27,753
HUH?
[WHISTLES]
ALL RIGHT, HERE IT COMES.

262
00:13:27,786 --> 00:13:29,353
- THIS IS IT, BOYS.
EVERYONE AT THE READY.

263
00:13:29,386 --> 00:13:30,786
GET READY.
- [PEOPLE SPEAKING AT ONCE]

264
00:13:30,819 --> 00:13:32,853
- STEP OUT OF THE VEHICLE.
- GET HIM OUT OF THERE.

265
00:13:32,886 --> 00:13:35,319
[SHOUTING]

266
00:13:35,353 --> 00:13:37,219
- OH, NO!
NO!

267
00:13:37,253 --> 00:13:41,053
WE'VE GOT TO GO HOME!
- [SHOUTING]

268
00:13:41,853 --> 00:13:43,553
- IT'S TAKING OVER!
- UH--UHH!

269
00:13:43,586 --> 00:13:48,453
- WHAT IS THAT?
OH, MY--
[SHOUTING]

270
00:14:00,619 --> 00:14:03,819
- BEWARE OF THE FLESH-EATING
NOH MASK.

271
00:14:03,853 --> 00:14:07,619
BEWARE OF THE NOH MASK!

272
00:14:14,753 --> 00:14:15,853
[SCREAMING]

273
00:14:15,886 --> 00:14:19,553
- UHH!
[GLASS CLINKS]

274
00:14:23,253 --> 00:14:25,553
A NOH MASK?
THAT MUST BE
THE FLESH-EATING MASK

275
00:14:25,586 --> 00:14:28,719
THAT GRANDPA WAS MUMBLING ABOUT
IN THE HOSPITAL.

276
00:14:28,753 --> 00:14:30,186
AAH!

277
00:14:32,619 --> 00:14:33,486
- JEWEL.

278
00:14:33,519 --> 00:14:37,619
I MUST HAVE THE SHARDS
OF THE SHIKON JEWEL.

279
00:14:38,053 --> 00:14:40,219
- UH...UHH.

280
00:14:40,253 --> 00:14:42,719
- GIVE ME THE PIECES
OF THE SHIKON JEWEL!

281
00:14:42,753 --> 00:14:46,686
- COME ON, SOTA.
THIS IS NO TIME
TO ZONE OUT ON ME.

282
00:14:46,719 --> 00:14:48,786
WE'VE GOT TO GET AWAY
FROM THE MASK.

283
00:14:48,819 --> 00:14:50,019
I HAVE TO CALL INUYASHA,

284
00:14:50,053 --> 00:14:53,553
'CAUSE HE'S THE ONLY ONE
WHO CAN HELP US.
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

285
00:14:53,586 --> 00:14:54,919
- KAGOME...
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

286
00:14:54,953 --> 00:14:57,553
LOOK AT YOUR FINGERS.
YOUR FINGERS ARE BLEEDING.

287
00:14:57,586 --> 00:15:01,686
- FORGET IT.
I CUT MYSELF ON THE GLASS,
THAT'S ALL.

288
00:15:04,286 --> 00:15:06,153
[BREATHING HEAVILY]
HUH?

289
00:15:06,186 --> 00:15:10,219
- HUH?
[SCREAMING]

290
00:15:11,486 --> 00:15:13,086
- THE JEWEL SHARDS.

291
00:15:13,119 --> 00:15:16,853
GIVE ME THE JEWEL SHARDS!

292
00:15:16,886 --> 00:15:19,853
- THE MASK HAS A JEWEL FRAGMENT
ON ITS FOREHEAD,

293
00:15:19,886 --> 00:15:21,519
SO THAT'S WHY IT'S
AFTER THESE SHARDS.

294
00:15:21,553 --> 00:15:25,386
I'VE GOT TO GET SOTA
AWAY FROM HERE
AND OUT OF DANGER!

295
00:15:25,419 --> 00:15:28,653
SOTA! RUN TO THE HIDDEN WELL
AND GET INUYASHA.

296
00:15:28,686 --> 00:15:30,419
TELL HIM THERE ARE
MORE JEWEL SHARDS HERE.

297
00:15:30,453 --> 00:15:34,753
THAT SHOULD BE ENOUGH TO GET HIM
TO CROSS OVER AND HELP US.

298
00:15:34,786 --> 00:15:36,719
- I HAVE TO GO
IN THAT SPOOKY WELL?

299
00:15:36,753 --> 00:15:39,786
- YOU CAN HANDLE IT.
JUST GET GOING!

300
00:15:41,119 --> 00:15:43,819
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

301
00:15:46,019 --> 00:15:48,453
[GULP]

302
00:15:50,419 --> 00:15:52,019
- I CAN HANDLE THIS.

303
00:15:52,053 --> 00:15:54,686
YAAA!

304
00:15:54,719 --> 00:15:56,653
[CRASH]
- BLAH! OOH.

305
00:15:56,686 --> 00:15:59,586
HOW COME I'M STILL HERE?

306
00:15:59,619 --> 00:16:02,219
- WAH!
WHAT WENT WRONG?

307
00:16:02,253 --> 00:16:04,753
- [MEOWING]

308
00:16:04,786 --> 00:16:06,253
- I'VE GOT TO GET
THROUGH THE WELL,

309
00:16:06,286 --> 00:16:08,019
'CAUSE SIS IS IN TROUBLE.

310
00:16:08,053 --> 00:16:08,986
THE MASK IS AFTER HER,

311
00:16:09,019 --> 00:16:13,619
AND I'M THE ONLY ONE
WHO CAN HELP.
[SOBBING]

312
00:16:16,386 --> 00:16:18,853
H-HUH?

313
00:16:21,319 --> 00:16:24,453
IT'S YOU.
YOU'RE INUYASHA.

314
00:16:24,486 --> 00:16:25,386
- IN THE FLESH, KID.

315
00:16:25,419 --> 00:16:28,953
NOW WHAT'S THIS PROBLEM
YOU NEED HELP WITH?

316
00:16:28,986 --> 00:16:30,986
UHH. UHH.
UHH.

317
00:16:31,019 --> 00:16:33,086
HANG ON TIGHT, KID.
IT'S A LONG WAY DOWN.

318
00:16:33,119 --> 00:16:37,153
- I GUESS I WASN'T STRONG ENOUGH
TO PASS THROUGH THE HIDDEN WELL.

319
00:16:37,186 --> 00:16:38,519
- LUCKY FOR YOU,

320
00:16:38,553 --> 00:16:41,386
BECAUSE IN MY WORLD,
THERE ARE PLENTY OF MONSTERS

321
00:16:41,419 --> 00:16:43,953
WHO'D JUST LOVE
TO HAVE YOU FOR LUNCH.

322
00:16:43,986 --> 00:16:46,753
- GUH--
- UHH.

323
00:16:46,786 --> 00:16:47,586
UHH.

324
00:16:47,619 --> 00:16:50,553
- DO YOU KNOW
WHERE TO FIND MY SISTER?

325
00:16:50,586 --> 00:16:51,953
- SURE.
I'M NOT HUMAN, REMEMBER?

326
00:16:51,986 --> 00:16:54,986
I CAN PICK UP SCENTS
FROM MILES AROUND
WITH THIS NOSE.

327
00:16:55,019 --> 00:16:56,453
- KAGOME CUT HER HAND
ON SOME GLASS.

328
00:16:56,486 --> 00:17:00,119
- DON'T HAVE TO TELL ME THAT.
I CAN SMELL THE BLOOD
FROM BACK IN THE WELL.

329
00:17:00,153 --> 00:17:02,086
FEAR NOT.
I'LL RESCUE KAGOME

330
00:17:02,119 --> 00:17:04,519
BEFORE SHE GETS INTO
ANY REAL TROUBLE.

331
00:17:04,553 --> 00:17:05,686
- I'LL TELL YOU WHAT HE'S LIKE.

332
00:17:05,719 --> 00:17:09,186
HE'S WHINY AND A SHOW-OFF
AND A TOTAL EGOMANIAC.

333
00:17:09,219 --> 00:17:11,053
[SIGH]
THE GUY'S A COMPLETE PAIN.

334
00:17:11,086 --> 00:17:14,219
- THIS CAN'T BE THE SAME GUY
KAGOME WAS TELLING ME ABOUT.

335
00:17:14,253 --> 00:17:15,853
SURE, HIS OUTFIT'S
A BIT OUT OF DATE,

336
00:17:15,886 --> 00:17:18,253
BUT INUYASHA'S
THE ONLY GUY AROUND HERE

337
00:17:18,286 --> 00:17:20,353
I THINK I CAN TRUST.

338
00:17:30,727 --> 00:17:33,427
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

339
00:17:33,927 --> 00:17:35,594
- INUYASHA'S NOT HERE YET.

340
00:17:35,627 --> 00:17:38,460
WHAT'S TAKING HIM SO LONG?

341
00:17:41,127 --> 00:17:42,827
AAH!

342
00:17:45,360 --> 00:17:46,960
AAH!

343
00:17:47,594 --> 00:17:48,427
OH, NO!

344
00:17:48,460 --> 00:17:52,294
- I NEED THE SHARDS
OF THE SHIKON JEWEL!

345
00:17:52,327 --> 00:17:55,694
- IRON REAPER SOUL STEALER!

346
00:17:59,727 --> 00:18:02,127
- NICE TIMING.
- YOU ALL RIGHT?

347
00:18:02,160 --> 00:18:05,094
- SURE. I'M FINE.
- OH, SIS.

348
00:18:05,127 --> 00:18:06,794
- HEY, WHAT'S WITH
ALL THE TEARS?

349
00:18:06,827 --> 00:18:07,927
I THOUGHT YOU SAID
YOU WEREN'T AFRAID.

350
00:18:07,960 --> 00:18:11,460
- IT'S OK.
INUYASHA'S GONNA DESTROY
THAT MONSTER FOR US,

351
00:18:11,494 --> 00:18:14,360
AND IT'LL ALL BE OVER.
- AHEM.
- HUH?

352
00:18:14,394 --> 00:18:16,927
- BEFORE WE GET ON
WITH MY LITTLE
RESCUE MISSION HERE,

353
00:18:16,960 --> 00:18:20,360
THIS MIGHT BE AN APPROPRIATE
TIME FOR AN APOLOGY,
WOULDN'T YOU SAY?

354
00:18:20,394 --> 00:18:22,694
- HUH?
APOLOGY FOR WHAT?

355
00:18:22,727 --> 00:18:23,694
SIT!

356
00:18:23,727 --> 00:18:25,827
- FOR WHAT?
FOR SHOUTING
ALL THOSE INCANTATIONS

357
00:18:25,860 --> 00:18:28,160
AND PUTTING MY BACK OUT,
THAT'S WHAT.

358
00:18:28,194 --> 00:18:30,994
YEAH, SHE HAS THE GALL
TO BEG ME FOR HELP.

359
00:18:31,027 --> 00:18:33,927
- OH, THAT.
YEAH, NOW IT'S COMING BACK.

360
00:18:33,960 --> 00:18:36,494
OK. I'M VERY SORRY.
THERE. YOU SATISFIED NOW?

361
00:18:36,527 --> 00:18:40,927
- SHE MAKES IT SOUND LIKE
SHE'S APOLOGIZING FOR
STEPPING ON MY FOOT.

362
00:18:40,960 --> 00:18:42,260
MAYBE I'LL GO BACK.

363
00:18:42,294 --> 00:18:43,427
- YOU CAN'T JUST LEAVE US HERE.

364
00:18:43,460 --> 00:18:45,960
BESIDES, THE MASK HAS A SHARD
OF THE SACRED JEWEL.

365
00:18:45,994 --> 00:18:48,060
DON'T YOU WANT TO ADD IT
TO OUR COLLECTION?

366
00:18:48,094 --> 00:18:48,927
- HMPH.
- HMPH!

367
00:18:48,960 --> 00:18:50,327
- SO HE'S REFUSING TO SAVE US

368
00:18:50,360 --> 00:18:52,060
OVER A LITTLE APOLOGY?

369
00:18:52,094 --> 00:18:53,327
WHAT HAPPENED TO MY HERO?

370
00:18:53,360 --> 00:18:55,394
HE'S SHRINKING
TO LIFE-SIZE PROPORTIONS

371
00:18:55,427 --> 00:18:57,060
BEFORE MY VERY EYES.

372
00:18:57,094 --> 00:18:58,527
- OH, NO.
THE MASK!

373
00:18:58,560 --> 00:19:01,427
- WHO DARES TO ATTACK ME?

374
00:19:01,460 --> 00:19:03,327
- INUYASHA, AIM FOR THE MASK.

375
00:19:03,360 --> 00:19:05,094
THE SHARD IS IN THE FOREHEAD!

376
00:19:05,127 --> 00:19:06,994
- I AM THE FLESH-EATING MASK.

377
00:19:07,027 --> 00:19:09,894
CENTURIES AGO, I WAS CARVED
FROM A GIANT TREE

378
00:19:09,927 --> 00:19:12,594
WHICH HAD A FRAGMENT
OF THE SACRED SHIKON JEWEL

379
00:19:12,627 --> 00:19:13,694
EMBEDDED IN IT.

380
00:19:13,727 --> 00:19:14,727
SINCE MY CREATION,

381
00:19:14,760 --> 00:19:18,427
I HAVE CRAVED HUMAN FLESH
AND DEVOURED MY VICTIMS.

382
00:19:18,460 --> 00:19:21,827
BUT NOW, I WISH TO HAVE
A LIVING BODY THAT WILL NOT ROT.

383
00:19:21,860 --> 00:19:25,827
FOR THAT, I REQUIRE MORE POWER
FROM THE SACRED JEWEL.

384
00:19:25,860 --> 00:19:27,594
- I SEE.
SO THAT'S WHY THE MASK

385
00:19:27,627 --> 00:19:29,694
IS SO DESPERATE
TO HAVE THESE SHARDS.

386
00:19:29,727 --> 00:19:32,727
- I DON'T KNOW HOW MANY HUMANS
YOU'VE EATEN SO FAR,

387
00:19:32,760 --> 00:19:36,827
BUT IT'S TIME
TO LOSE SOME WEIGHT!

388
00:19:38,094 --> 00:19:38,860
WHAT THE...

389
00:19:38,894 --> 00:19:40,794
- YOU FELL INTO MY TRAP.

390
00:19:40,827 --> 00:19:44,160
NOW YOU SHALL NEVER ESCAPE ME.

391
00:19:44,194 --> 00:19:45,860
- AAH!

392
00:19:45,894 --> 00:19:47,560
[GASP]
- INUYASHA!

393
00:19:47,594 --> 00:19:49,760
[GRUNTING]

394
00:19:49,794 --> 00:19:52,394
- I SHOULD'VE KNOWN BETTER.

395
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:56,427
- AAH!
UHH!

396
00:19:56,460 --> 00:19:58,694
- KAGOME!
- UHH! UHH!

397
00:19:58,727 --> 00:20:01,327
I CAN'T LET THIS THING
GET THE JEWELS!

398
00:20:01,360 --> 00:20:04,094
SOTA, TAKE THESE SHARDS AND RUN!

399
00:20:04,127 --> 00:20:05,860
- OK.
- HURRY!

400
00:20:05,894 --> 00:20:07,227
- UHH--UHH.

401
00:20:07,260 --> 00:20:09,960
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

402
00:20:10,560 --> 00:20:13,194
- IT'S RIGHT BEHIND YOU!

403
00:20:15,127 --> 00:20:18,294
[BREATHING HEAVILY]
- AAH! UHH.

404
00:20:18,794 --> 00:20:20,694
THE MASK IS AFTER THIS BOTTLE.

405
00:20:20,727 --> 00:20:22,827
I'LL THROW IT AWAY.
NO, THAT WON'T WORK.

406
00:20:22,860 --> 00:20:27,060
I CAN'T LET IT HAVE
THESE JEWELS!
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

407
00:20:30,160 --> 00:20:31,594
- AAH!

408
00:20:31,627 --> 00:20:33,394
- UHH!

409
00:20:34,027 --> 00:20:36,260
DON'T MOVE, KID!

410
00:20:37,260 --> 00:20:40,127
- YAA!
- AAH! AAH!

411
00:20:42,694 --> 00:20:45,060
UHH!
UHH.

412
00:20:46,760 --> 00:20:48,394
[CLINK]

413
00:20:48,427 --> 00:20:52,160
- YOU DESTROYED THE MASK!
YOU DID IT!

414
00:20:52,194 --> 00:20:55,827
- SURE THING.
YOU STILL GOT THOSE
JEWEL FRAGMENTS?

415
00:20:55,860 --> 00:20:59,460
[GULP]
HMM...YEAH.

416
00:21:01,727 --> 00:21:02,560
- INUYASHA!

417
00:21:02,594 --> 00:21:04,460
- HEY, KAGOME.
YOU ALL RIGHT?

418
00:21:04,494 --> 00:21:05,527
HOW'S YOUR HAND?

419
00:21:05,560 --> 00:21:07,927
- UH, FINE.

420
00:21:07,960 --> 00:21:09,360
OK, THIS IS WEIRD.

421
00:21:09,394 --> 00:21:11,727
WHEN DID INUYASHA
START BEING SO NICE?

422
00:21:11,760 --> 00:21:14,960
I MEAN, NOT SO NICE,
BUT KIND OF NICE.

423
00:21:14,994 --> 00:21:16,527
AND MAYBE IT'S JUST
THE MORNING LIGHT,

424
00:21:16,560 --> 00:21:20,027
BUT HE LOOKS PRETTY COOL
STANDING THERE WITH HIS SWORD.

425
00:21:20,060 --> 00:21:21,327
WAIT A MINUTE.
MORNING LIGHT?

426
00:21:21,360 --> 00:21:24,960
OH, NO!
IT'S MORNING ALREADY, AND I
HAVEN'T STUDIED FOR MY TEST!

427
00:21:24,994 --> 00:21:27,694
OHH!
- HEY, WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

428
00:21:27,727 --> 00:21:29,194
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

429
00:21:29,227 --> 00:21:31,127
- THANKS, INUYASHA.
IT'S BEEN A SLICE.

430
00:21:31,160 --> 00:21:33,194
SEE YOU WHEN I SEE YA.
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

431
00:21:33,227 --> 00:21:36,627
OH, AND SOTA, DON'T FORGET
TO PICK UP THOSE JEWEL SHARDS

432
00:21:36,660 --> 00:21:37,927
AND BRING THEM HOME WITH YOU.

433
00:21:37,960 --> 00:21:39,427
INUYASHA, I'M GOING
TO BE SUPER MAD

434
00:21:39,460 --> 00:21:42,727
IF YOU'RE STILL AROUND
WHEN I GET BACK FROM SCHOOL.

435
00:21:42,760 --> 00:21:44,560
- HMM?
- KNOW WHAT?

436
00:21:44,594 --> 00:21:48,994
I'VE GOT A NEW HERO,
BET YOU CAN'T GUESS WHO IT IS.

437
00:21:49,027 --> 00:21:50,994
- OH, MAN.

438
00:21:51,027 --> 00:21:52,660
- IN EVERY
RIGHT-ANGLED TRIANGLE,

439
00:21:52,694 --> 00:21:54,027
